Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.66,0:00:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I screwed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.02,0:00:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That one actually had me worried there \Nfor a second, primitive creatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.69,0:01:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I steal those genes, \Nthis planet is dust!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.78,0:02:48.17,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Defensive Battle at Cosmopolitan Academy\N (Second Part)"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.28,0:03:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It missed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.87,0:03:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.07,0:03:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move it, primitive creature!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you get your \Nhands on our school!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.84,0:03:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4's Mobile Assembly \NExtreme Range Cannon
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.98,0:03:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has begun recharging.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.65,0:03:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will be done in 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5's Harmonic Level is \Ncontinuing to increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.98,0:03:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not sure if he can \Nsustain this for very long...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.57,0:03:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1, Rose 3, once you've \Neliminated your targets,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.10,0:03:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go offer Red 5 support!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.78,0:03:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.08,0:03:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, what are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3 isn't flying right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.35,0:03:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The unit musta gotten damaged here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.73,0:03:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there when we \Nentered the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, of all the times...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang tight, Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.27,0:04:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Hurry! Hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.30,0:04:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please hurry and charge up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to send you some \Nof Purple 2's energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.49,0:04:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should cut your charge time a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All pit ships, direct your \Nenergy to him as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relay the energy to Gold \N4 through Purple 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.33,0:04:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirming receipt of \Nthe microwave energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.93,0:04:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Firing the energy to Gold 4!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.46,0:04:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.77,0:04:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, isn't this dangerously fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't make it in time if \Nwe wait for a full recharge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But without sufficient power,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.62,0:05:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we can't shoot that enemy down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your pathetic weapons can't harm me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the end of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.49,0:06:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, Tamaki, now! Attack him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better dodge this, Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.51,0:06:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many of you face \Nme, the outcome will be the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please go straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.37,0:06:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I'm going \Nto run out of energy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to stop him, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, ram into him from behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.78,0:06:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.70,0:06:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.79,0:06:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suruga, what's your energy at?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.33,0:06:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 70%. It still isn't enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.87,0:06:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Tamaki makes contact with \NKlein's unit, shoot Rose 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, Izuru and Asagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.98,0:06:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you are to help Tamaki escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot Rose 3...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.01,0:06:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.34,0:06:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.41,0:06:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4 is on the brink of overloading
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.18,0:06:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,due to forcing it to recharge too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.02,0:06:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our last chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:07:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There won't be any second \Nchances if I miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.89,0:07:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Ataru Suruga!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.08,0:07:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.03,0:07:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.41,0:07:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sight's precision is improving!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.98,0:07:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could the pilot's heightened \Nconcentration have something to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.94,0:07:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4's Harmonic Level \Nis also increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.42,0:07:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is his highest level thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.23,0:07:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.15,0:07:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These feeble attacks-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you plotting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, eject!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.05,0:09:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy squad has been \Ncompletely subdued!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.51,0:09:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All five members of Team \NRabbits are unharmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They did it, Rin-Rin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.05,0:09:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but it was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.36,0:09:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the extent of your power?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show me what you're made of!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.35,0:09:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven't given \Nme a flippin' good fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.27,0:09:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need more freakin' fighting spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.11,0:09:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab a pair of balls and come at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.24,0:10:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see Tamaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.96,0:10:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.17,0:10:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which side's winning down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.29,0:10:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure, but the battle \Non Earth should be over soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.76,0:10:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Rabbits wins, it should
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.41,0:10:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,influence our battle \Nhere on the frontlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.47,0:10:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! The enemy is \Nstarting to pull back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.77,0:10:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Izuru and the \Nothers won their battle, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.23,0:10:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of you better be alive \Nand hoppin', Bunnies!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klein's squad was annihilated?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid it would seem that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.93,0:10:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are approaching the limit to \Nhow long we can remain active.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May we receive permission \Nto return to base?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Permission to \Nreturn has been granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall take a different route back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will see you in person shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.39,0:11:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the time to implement \Nhis plan has come...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fully dismantle each unit and \Ngive them thorough checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Identify everything that \Nneeds to be replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.17,0:11:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For anything lacking a spare,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.18,0:11:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,contact Earth and have them \Nsend a replacement immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They might have to sortie again soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.34,0:11:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commence repair work at full power!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.47,0:11:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It took an even worse \Nbeating than usual, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.26,0:11:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna be up all night!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we should be grateful that \NIzu-boing came back safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.59,0:11:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof that we've done a \Ngood job maintaining this puppy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.10,0:11:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Now it's our turn to hop to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.94,0:11:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys have it good...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can jump straight to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.87,0:12:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minus Rose 3's core, everything \Nis still in pieces down on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.74,0:12:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.28,0:12:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The core was all that survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.13,0:12:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything else has to \Nbe remade from scratch!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish we could fly to \NEarth right this second
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.73,0:12:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and retrieve the battered \Nand beaten Rose 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.31,0:12:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.83,0:12:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our little lady is all right, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.53,0:12:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! Her unit may have \Nbeen terribly damaged,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I've heard that our pilot \Nwalked away without a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.85,0:12:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a relief!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.03,0:12:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything happened to \Nher, it'd be our fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.81,0:12:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to hold a party to \Ncelebrate her victory later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.18,0:12:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With a cake and tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.64,0:12:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that our \NSuruga was a big help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It proves that our theory was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.72,0:12:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, even sniping \Nrelies on physical prowess!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His daily bodybuilding workouts \Nwith us are starting to pay off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.65,0:12:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's double our workout routine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.38,0:12:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two sets of 100 push-ups and \Ntwo sets of 100 sit-ups!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone sure is hyped up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's normal for people to act \Nthis way after winning a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.17,0:12:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izu-boing and the others \Ndid their best out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:13:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's our turn to \Nstep up and work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.59,0:13:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet they're sound \Nasleep in bed by now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shock from the blast destroyed \Nliterally all of the school's windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.35,0:13:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The building was also destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.06,0:13:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise, the inner facilities \Nwere substantially damaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.77,0:13:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, you made a massive \Ncrater on school grounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.94,0:13:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, the outer \Nwalls were also damaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.65,0:13:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1 and Red 5's transport chains \Nare damaged in countless locations!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.27,0:13:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2 and Gold 4 were mostly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.97,0:13:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,destroyed by the shock created \Nwhen the Mobile Assembly
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.61,0:13:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Extreme Range Cannon exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.08,0:13:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for Rose 3, aside from the core, it \Nwas essentially blown to smithereens!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.03,0:13:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to take a long time before \Nall of the spare parts come in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and your units are made \Noperational again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... But, hey, we \Nprotected the academy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.32,0:13:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should be happy it \Ndidn't turn out worse...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are limits to such things!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.34,0:13:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you have done if \Nyou destroyed the school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.74,0:13:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.06,0:13:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you did a good job out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Job well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:13:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Job well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.02,0:14:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Job well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Job well-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.14,0:14:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fall asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.66,0:14:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki Irie, would you like \Nto hang out with me tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.46,0:14:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki Irie, would you like \Nto hang out with me tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to hold \Nhis hand like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.50,0:14:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're a team, \Nwe're as good as family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We live and die together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.55,0:14:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo! Great work out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-thank you. I'm honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.32,0:14:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to hang \Nout with me tomorrow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not what I meant! That was a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That didn't happen! Scratch that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, you need to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.01,0:14:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should pull back for \Nnow and regain your bearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a tactical retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.61,0:14:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we'll chill out with \Nyou some other time, 'kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Consequentially, the \Nenemy forces retreated,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the allied armies \Nsuffered immense losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.04,0:15:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth's forces have been \Ndiminished to next to nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The masses seem to be \Ngreatly distraught as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.42,0:15:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So their sense of danger \Nis beginning to escalate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.84,0:15:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until now, they probably considered \Nthis on the same level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.72,0:15:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as military terrorists in \Nthe far reaches of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since this last attack was a \Ndirect assault on Earth itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.77,0:15:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And nothing but the AHSMB seem to \Nbe effective against the Wulgaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. If we don't start \Nmass producing them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But will that alone be enough \Nto drive the enemy away?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.16,0:15:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just received an encrypted \Nmessage from Legatus Lumes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that was hidden in a \Ntransmission from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.94,0:15:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From Lumes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he came into contact with \None of Earth's data devices,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would seem that he infiltrated \Nand tampered with the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.17,0:15:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, he gave the \Nimpression that he was already
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,aware of your presence on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.22,0:15:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he has found out about us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:15:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I came prepared to \Nface the consequences...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.02,0:16:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the transmission,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.32,0:16:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your brother is waiting \Nto hear from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How would you like me to respond?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so much as a single unit \Nfrom Klein's squad returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! Although they \Nreaped what they sowed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it nonetheless pains my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.33,0:16:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lose an entire squad led \Nby a Military Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bluntly put, the position \Nas Military Commander
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.23,0:16:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was too great for Klein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.10,0:16:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a disgrace to the Wulgaru race.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.72,0:16:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, we must choose someone \Na bit more worthy of the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.51,0:16:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One who has not been fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.34,0:16:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has no right to say such things, Lutiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.54,0:16:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you get down to it, \Nwas there a stock of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.06,0:16:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,DNA on the primitives' \Nhome world or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.65,0:16:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I am afraid we were \Nunable to verify that information.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't we hurry and \Nsend out the next squad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.15,0:16:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, I'd be willing \Nto dispatch the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:16:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After this incident, I imagine \NEarth will be on heightened alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we should wait and \Nwatch for a while first.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a boring and cautious plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.87,0:17:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.54,0:17:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one thing I wish to report.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took a look at Klein's battle \Nrecords from his last skirmish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.59,0:17:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've noticed that the humans \Nfrequently sacrifice themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.26,0:17:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to rescue another individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To meet those ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.34,0:17:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sometimes they take unexpected \Nmeasures to throw us into confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that simply prove \Nthat they are lower animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than leisurely biding our time,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.68,0:17:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should finish them \Noff in one fell swoop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In certain aspects, the Earthlings \Nvary from other species
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.18,0:17:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we have encountered in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.41,0:17:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot afford another mishap \Nlike with Legatus Klein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.53,0:17:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in regard to Legatus Dolgana's \Nobservation earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.59,0:17:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About how the Earthlings \Ndefend one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.72,0:18:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.04,0:18:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would seem that someone else \Nhas finally noticed that trait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.64,0:18:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you had already noticed \Nthis, Prince Jiart?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.81,0:18:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.44,0:18:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usually, intelligent creatures have a \Ntendency to develop overall equally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If one forms a weakness, its own \Nkind will target that individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.37,0:18:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if, one was guaranteed \Nto not be attacked by the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.20,0:18:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The various individuals \Ncould develop their talents,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,allowing them to compensate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.89,0:18:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for their weaknesses while \Nfunctioning in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would almost be as if \Nthey were one life form...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.80,0:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.22,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the animals possess a certain \Ndegree of intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is only natural for the species
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to begin warring amongst \Nthemselves for personal gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.52,0:18:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.81,0:18:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cooperation is only a possibility if
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.50,0:18:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,both sides have something \Nsubstantial to gain from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.06,0:18:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As is the case with my clan and yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.65,0:19:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My family has served your clan \Nfor generations, Prince Jiart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.24,0:19:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am grateful that you \Nallow me to serve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.12,0:19:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Earthlings are \Ncompletely alien to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.14,0:19:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is precisely \Nwhat makes them amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.04,0:19:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it you were unable \Nto make contact with Teoria?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.38,0:19:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct. Instead I followed \Nyour instructions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.58,0:19:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sent a transmission to Daneel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.83,0:19:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,through the Earth's \Ncommunications circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.28,0:19:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I was unable to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.48,0:19:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,confirm whether he received the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.87,0:19:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take it no one noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.93,0:19:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, not even King Galkie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall give Teoria some \Ntime to see how she responds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rada!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.20,0:19:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he overheard us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.98,0:19:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you have me do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.54,0:19:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned something I shouldn't have!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.80,0:19:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.29,0:19:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:20:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Legatus Rada, under orders by Pleguzes \NJiart, you are under arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.18,0:20:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under arrest?! What have I done?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.82,0:20:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take your question \Ndirectly to Pleguzes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.35,0:20:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Treason," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.85,0:20:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Legatus Rada just came before \NPleguzes Jiart and me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and invited us to join him as \Nconspirators in his rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we rejected his offer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.45,0:20:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are currently tracking Rada down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.86,0:20:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rada did that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.57,0:20:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleguzes Jiart requests that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.89,0:20:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you leave the matter to his discretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.50,0:20:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. It is in his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.89,0:20:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you perceive this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The weak always lose. \NIt's as simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.08,0:20:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He outmaneuvered me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.52,0:20:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?! Where can I run?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.33,0:21:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must hurry and inform King Galkie!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.44,0:21:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.65,0:21:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must hurry or else...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.43,0:21:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't I getting through?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.25,0:21:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come after me! Don't! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.05,0:21:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I'll use that gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.30,0:21:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can just make it through that...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.14,0:21:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.50,0:22:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Wulgaru way, Teoria...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:55.95,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Deep Recon"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.95,0:23:57.95,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,
